Job Description:
Advise the GD on organizational structure and the improvement of management regulations and company procedures:
- Propose organizational structure and define the functions and responsibilities of departments;
- Develop and improve policies on human resource development, benefits, compensation, management regulations, internal rules, and workflows;
- Plan and organize recruitment and training activities;
- Monitor and forecast personnel changes (transfers, increases, reductions, adjustments);
- Issue and oversee the implementation of company regulations.

Organize implementation and manage operation of HR works:
- Recruitment
- Train and develop human resources;
- Implement labor policies and regimes: salaries, bonuses, benefits, insurance, and monthly personal income tax payments, as well as compile related reports;
- Evaluate employee performance;
- Sign, renew, and terminate labor contracts;
- Transfer and adjust personnel (appointments, dismissals, salary/bonus/benefit increases or reductions);
- Manage and utilize human resource data;
- Calculate salaries, allowances, employee benefits, and personal income tax.

Management and supervision of general administrative operations:
- Develop and monitor the implementation of administrative expense plans
- Procure and distribute work equipment for employees
- Monitor and manage company assets, including maintenance, repair, handover, and usage supervision
- Supervise the operation of office services (electricity, water, office supplies, shuttle services, visas/residency for foreigners, printing, copying, internet, etc.)
- Oversee document archiving, translation of company materials, and the use of company data and documents
- Track and apply for visas, work permits, and temporary residence cards for foreign employees

Others:
- Cooperate, coordinate with other departments in building company cultures, business relationship with partners, local authorities
- Other works under the request and assignment from GD

Reporting:
- Report of daily work to Vice General Director and General Director (as specific order)
- Report in coordination with other departments as scope of work assigned

• Chịu trách nhiệm thiết kế các ấn phẩm (poster, tờ rơi, standee, backdrop, bandroll, thư mời, ...) hỗ trợ cho việc quảng bá, tổ chức sự kiện, hoạt động kinh doanh của công ty;
• Thiết kế các ấn phẩm đồ họa: Logo, catalogue, nhận diện thương hiệu,...
• Thiết kế các mẫu quảng cáo, brochure, banner ... theo ý tưởng có trước;
• Thiết kế các ấn phẩm Digital truyền thông khác;
• Chụp ảnh, chỉnh sửa ảnh cho các sự kiện của thương hiệu, sự kiện nội bộ của công ty;
• Cùng triển khai các chương trình Marketing/PR cho các sự kiện, chiến dịch truyền thông của công ty;
• Chỉnh sửa, hoàn thiện sản phẩm theo yêu cầu;
• Quản lý chất lượng đối tác thiết kế đồ họa;
• Thực hiện các công việc theo sự phân công của quản lý.

Job Requirements:
REQUIREMENTS
• Bachelor's degree in Marketing field.
• Minimum of 1 year of experience in Marketing and Communications, preferably within a law firm or professional services environment.
• Strong experience in graphic design, video editing, and using AI tools to support media production.
• Strong presentation and interpersonal skills.
• Ability to multitask and prioritize tasks in a fast-paced environment.
• Good communication skills in English and Vietnamese (both writing and speaking).

BENEFITS
• Competitive salary depending on capacity, experience, and attractive bonus, with various remuneration regimes;
• Working in an international, professional, and civilized environment;
• Working side by side with experienced, passionate, and dynamic colleagues;
• Opportunities for career development and self-advancement;
• Being entitled to welfare regimes following the company's regulations.

• Tối thiểu 3 năm kinh nghiệm trong lĩnh vực quản lý bán lẻ, chuỗi cửa hàng hoặc vận hành mô hình O2O;
• Hiểu rõ về chiến lược và cách triển khai trải nghiệm khách hàng đa kênh;
• Có kỹ năng giao tiếp và xử lý vấn đề tốt;
• Có khả năng đào tạo đội nhóm và vận hành hệ thống;
